Name: Unknown
Description: Unknown encounter role for legacy providers with no encounter role set

Name: Dispenser
Description: Provider that dispenses medications or other products

Name: Nurse
Description: A person educated and trained to care for the sick or disabled.

Name: Nurse Midwife
Description: A person educated and trained in midwifery.

Name: Consulting Clinician
Description: Clinician who is primarily responsible for examining and diagnosing a patient

Name: Administrative Clerk
Description: This role is used for creating a Check-in encounter

Name: Ordering Provider
Description: For encounters associated with orders, used to store the provider responsible for placing the order

Name: Attending Surgeon
Description: The surgeon with primary responsibility for the care of a patient in a particular surgery.

Name: Anesthesiologist
Description: Anesthesiologists are physicians who delivering anesthesia during surgical procedures, care for critically ill patients in an ICU, manage medical emergencies, and pain management.

Name: Assisting Surgeon
Description: Additional surgeons (beyond the Attending Surgeon) who assist in a surgery.

Name: Radiology Technician
Description: Radiology Technician - person who performs radiology studies

Name: Principal Results Interpreter
Description: Principal Results Interpreter - the provider responsible for interpreting the results of a radiology study
